caption: Surely a spot worth stopping by, the food is excellent and fresh, the pricing is fair and it is regularly well kept there. Kudos.

Ordered through delivery.com.. Waited an hour, then called and was told that the driver tried to deliver a half an hour ago and had to wait a long time, and that my food may be in the public lobby. No one called me!  They said they would call the driver to see what happened. When they called back they told me that the food was actually delivered to the wrong apartment, and that I should just go get it!... During this pandemic!!  I don't know how long this stranger has been sitting with my food, what they touched or  tasted, or if the food has been eaten....  Disgusting attitude with no apologies for their error! I used to order from them all the time! This will be the last!!
Prices are fair. Good and fast service. And delicious food I have had sushi other places before but here has the some of the best especially they sweet potato sushi
Great quality sushi for the price. They do their own delivery which came quickly (I live <1 block away). Very happy to live so close to this place!
I love their sushi rolls. Juicy fresh fish fluffy rice. Great rolls.Years ago I thought of this place as ok backup sushi. Now they are perfect.

Not good.  Tom yum had no hint of spice, no lemongrass flavor. And had green peppers in it!  The ramen I'll admit is up against tough competition in Toto Ramen, but I didn't want to drive 45 minutes into Manhattan. Now I realize I should have.  Still in search of good ramen in Flatbush.
Dirty bad food and rude employees

So this is not my favorite sushi spot but this is a place where I will go whenever I'm in a hurry or in the neighborhood. I watched the guys as they prepare my Sushi to make sure that no one while handling my Sushi touches their nose face hair or anyting. I never seen this done with the guys who handle my food so I'm going to give them one star the second star comes because the food is actually good it is prepared fresh and when I do order a hot meal it is delivered hot. The third star is because of location. Customer service needs to be improved upon due to the cashier as well as I'm going to assume the person was one of the chefs... Non personable people
This spot is worth giving a shot. They have big portions for fair rates. Constantly neat and with awesome vibes. Would recommend to others.

The single worst place the manager is horrible didn't even get to test the food because the manager hang up the phone on me twice. Was going to make an order for about 120 dollars. What a mess up just for a manager that is disrespectful.

Got delivery,  food came quick and taste great! Prices are reasonable and the utensils came in a mini ziplock bag makes me feel like everything is clean and handle with care which is ultra important durnign time of covid!

I GOT DIARRHEA BOTH TIMES! Ive eaten there twice and have gotten diarrhea both times. Each time I have had the chicken Katsu and the softshell crab. Other than the sickness the food is not that tasty and pretty bland.

This restaurant has one of the best ramen in Brooklyn the red thai curry ramen The food is super good but the service is the worst We order a delivery and the food come super cold we call back and just a sorry I understand that maybe they are busy thanks to the pandemic but at least they can be honest and say we busy the food its gonna take a while or just make sure is gonna arrive hot!!! In its heyday (circa 2009), Sushi Tatsu was a happening place. It was nicely decorated and the food was tasty.  A good sum would dine there, especially during the warm weather when outside seating was available. Now, the interior is drab and the food less tasty.  The front door dons the letter "B" from the health department.  Today I ordered what was once my favorite: the Bento Box. I was adventurous and ordered the beef negimaki instead of the beef teriyaki. It was so so.
Good price and quality

Service was great and food was even better.
I am so happy to have the sushi restaurant near me. I can have my sushi every day. Yuuumm——
Great Sushi with great prices. I will be there every Friday for lunch. Place is not busy during lunch. Easy to go and get in and get out.

Everytime my partner and I come here we are taken care of very well.  The sushi, especially the California, spicy salmon, mango-avocado and eel rolls are incredibly delicious.  Both their miso soup and their side salad with carrot ginger dressing are amazing.  Bonus- you can choose either with a sushi combo, which is super affordable too!  This is also good for vegetarians as they have a large number of veggie sushi options.  If you are craving sushi, go here!
Food was good

I ordered $200 for a party of 30  people. Not only was there plenty of food but the quality was excellent and there were several seasoned compliments! Thank you Tatsu.
Nice food and nice costumer service totally recommend
Customer service is honestly amazing! And the food portions compared to other places are great. They give you your money's worth for sure! I come here all the time and it's fast and affordable.

This place is great, the staff is friendly-ish (just know beforehand what you want to order), the staff’s English isn’t that great but will understand you. The food is great but most of the fried food is just a tiny bit oily, all the rolls are affordable and tastes fresh. There’s very little to no wait time once you order your food.

I had the shrimp tempura ramen +spicy and a Philadelphia roll. The sushi came out first and was pretty good. The ramen was a good size for the price. I was skeptical ab putting the delicate tempura in the broth, fearful it would get soggy, but, alas, it did not. Those flavors belong together. The perfect amount of noodles and no wait, I'll definitely have to go back.

Only place with takoyaki in the area. Service is awesome and portions are large but food is just satisfactory. Would come back for the service and huge menu though!

The specialty rolls are really good but the normal cheaper rolls are lacking. Get specialty or something else other than sushi. The place has a chill ambiance and plenty of seating for a Brooklyn place.
